cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for facial expression recognition using deep convolutional neural networks and covariance descriptors. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of SVM with a valid Gaussian kernel on the SPD manifold suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the modeling of temporal dynamics of facial expressions suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
